devdoc.title: A bank contract that pays its users interest on a daily basis.

closeAccount().notice: Close bank account and return all user's balance to them. checks-effects-interaction pattern to prevent re-entrancy

enroll().notice: Enroll a customer with the bank

payInterest().notice: Pays interest to every account once criteria is met

poke().notice: Set 10 cents (USD) worth of ether. This will be called only by the oracle, and when the contract is not paused (circuit breaker pattern).

setMinBalance(uint256).notice: Set the minimum balance (USD, ETH) required to start receiving interest.

startPayments().notice: Start interest payments. Circuit breaker pattern used.

stopPayments().notice: Stop interest payments. Circuit breaker pattern used.

withdraw(uint256).notice: Withdraw ether from bank using pull pattern (to prevent re-entrancy) checks-effects-interaction pattern to prevent re-entrancy

userdoc.notice: Interest is based on maintaining a minumum balance in USD, which is converted to ETH using a rate fed into the contract by an Oracle. The rate is 10 cents (USD) of ETH.
